
[1]niggardly

   NIGGARDLY, a.

   1. Meanly covetous or avaricious; sordidly parsimonious; extremely
   sparing of expense.

   Where the owner of the house will be bountiful, it is not for the
   steward to be niggardly.

   2. Sparing; wary; cautiously avoiding profusion.

             NIGGARDLY, adv. Sparingly; with cautious parsimony.
